WEBVTT

00:01.080 --> 00:04.500
Dre: After taking the risk
of not going to college,

00:04.500 --> 00:07.420
Junior was doing
pretty good for himself.

00:07.420 --> 00:09.750
So, now when he comes over
with his new roommates,

00:09.750 --> 00:10.830
it's actually nice.

00:10.830 --> 00:12.170
Hey! What's up?

00:12.170 --> 00:14.250
-Hey!
-Hi, guys!

00:14.250 --> 00:15.670
-What's going on, young fella?
-Hi.

00:15.670 --> 00:18.540
Junior was finally
taking after me.

00:18.540 --> 00:22.120
For the first time in his life,
he was cool.

00:22.120 --> 00:24.210
I could see myself
hanging out with Junior --

00:24.210 --> 00:26.040
in public.

00:26.040 --> 00:28.790
I'd be willing to take pictures
and everything.

00:28.790 --> 00:31.580
I have to confess...
Mm-hmm?

00:31.580 --> 00:36.040
I am so proud of the man
that Junior has become.

00:36.040 --> 00:38.540
So am I!
I know, I know!

00:38.540 --> 00:41.290
Two Black friends
at the same time?
Two.

00:41.290 --> 00:42.710
Two!

00:42.710 --> 00:44.040
Oh, we've waited
for this!

00:44.040 --> 00:45.960
Whew.
Uh, hey, babe?

00:45.960 --> 00:48.040
Yeah.
I bought some
bubbly water yesterday.

00:48.040 --> 00:49.580
Did you move it?
Unh-unh.

00:49.580 --> 00:51.540
Look behind
the orange juice.
I can't.

00:51.540 --> 00:53.040
There isn't
any orange juice.

00:53.040 --> 00:54.880
What?
There isn't any cheese,

00:54.880 --> 00:57.290
and the soy sauce
is missing.
Unh-unh.

00:57.290 --> 00:58.710
I bought soy sauce
yesterday, babe.

00:58.710 --> 01:00.210
Wait a minute.

01:00.210 --> 01:01.620
Baby, there's --
there's no cereal,

01:01.620 --> 01:03.250
there's no honey.

01:03.250 --> 01:04.330
What?

01:04.330 --> 01:06.120
And is the sponge missing?
Where's the soap?

01:06.120 --> 01:07.500
Where's the --
where's the --

01:07.500 --> 01:08.960
Baby,
check the laundry room.

01:08.960 --> 01:10.000
Okay, okay, okay,
I'm checking.

01:10.000 --> 01:11.750
There's nothing down here!

01:11.750 --> 01:15.250
The only thing in here
is a sock and dryer lint.

01:15.250 --> 01:16.790
Where'd everything go?

01:16.790 --> 01:19.250
♪ Every day I'm hustling,
hustling, hustling ♪

01:19.250 --> 01:21.500
It was an
"Ocean's Eleven"-style set up

01:21.500 --> 01:24.460
from the jump.

01:24.460 --> 01:25.330
[ Watch beeps ]
And his boys were in on it.

01:25.330 --> 01:27.250
Hey, guys!

01:27.250 --> 01:30.080
Those friendly smiles
were just to disarm us.

01:30.080 --> 01:31.580
♪ Every day I'm hustling ♪

01:31.580 --> 01:33.670
♪ Who you suckers think
you're tripping with? ♪

01:33.670 --> 01:34.960
♪ Yes, I'm the boss ♪

01:34.960 --> 01:37.960
It was an inside job.

01:37.960 --> 01:40.420
Junior knew exactly
where we kept all the stuff

01:40.420 --> 01:41.920
broke kids never buy.

01:41.920 --> 01:44.500
Toilet paper,
canned goods, cinnamon.

01:44.500 --> 01:46.120
♪ We keep on coming back ♪

01:46.120 --> 01:47.830
♪ I'm into distribution ♪

01:47.830 --> 01:49.540
♪ I'm like Atlantic ♪

01:49.540 --> 01:51.460
They basically grabbed
the kitchen by the ankle

01:51.460 --> 01:52.960
and shook it.

01:52.960 --> 01:55.170
♪ I know Pablo ♪

01:55.170 --> 01:56.710
♪ Pablo ♪
♪ Noriega ♪

01:56.710 --> 01:59.120
♪ The real Noriega,
he owe me a hundred favors ♪

01:59.120 --> 02:00.460
♪ Every day
I'm hustling ♪

02:00.460 --> 02:02.460
I've got to give it up
to them,

02:02.460 --> 02:03.380
they were smooth.

02:03.380 --> 02:04.460
♪ Every day I'm hustling ♪

02:04.460 --> 02:06.790
Babe!

02:06.790 --> 02:08.790
We've been jacked!

02:11.460 --> 02:13.710
♪♪

02:13.710 --> 02:15.790
When did they go upstairs?
I don't know.

02:15.790 --> 02:17.620
My in-shower moisturizing gel
is missing.

02:17.620 --> 02:19.120
Do you know
what that means?

02:19.120 --> 02:21.120
That your feet are gonna
cut me in the night?

02:21.120 --> 02:24.460
No, that means
they went "in shower"!

02:24.460 --> 02:26.170
How did they know
I wasn't up there naked?

02:26.170 --> 02:27.250
Because you were down here.

02:27.250 --> 02:28.880
I still feel violated.

02:28.880 --> 02:29.880
Okay.

02:29.880 --> 02:32.330
They took the dried mangos.

02:32.330 --> 02:34.170
Oh, no, man, nah.
That wasn't part of the deal.

02:34.170 --> 02:35.670
What are you
talking about?

02:35.670 --> 02:36.750
[ Sighs ]

02:36.750 --> 02:38.540
I wasn't gonna snitch,

02:38.540 --> 02:40.670
but now I'm eating
plantain chips like a jerk,

02:40.670 --> 02:41.750
so screw it.

02:41.750 --> 02:43.080
Junior lost his job
with the Migos.

02:43.080 --> 02:44.750
What?
[ Door closes ]

02:44.750 --> 02:46.210
He can tell you.

02:46.210 --> 02:48.080
You lost your job?

02:48.080 --> 02:49.420
They took the mangos,
didn't they?

02:49.420 --> 02:50.540
Ya think?

02:50.540 --> 02:52.210
I swear...

02:52.210 --> 02:54.330
Hey, Junior,
when did this happen?

02:54.330 --> 02:56.170
Uh...

02:56.170 --> 02:58.170
Like, a couple of weeks ago,
I guess.

02:58.170 --> 03:00.080
I mean, there wasn't really
any paperwork.

03:00.080 --> 03:01.830
Offset kind of
just walked up to me

03:01.830 --> 03:03.750
and said, "Whomp, whomp,"
and patted me on the back.

03:03.750 --> 03:07.000
So, you were lying to us?

03:07.000 --> 03:10.290
Well, I thought I was gonna
find something else by now.

03:10.290 --> 03:12.120
But I have not.

03:12.120 --> 03:15.710
So you steal my almond-oil
moisturizing gel?

03:15.710 --> 03:18.710
How am I supposed
to exfoliate my back, son?

03:18.710 --> 03:20.120
With my hands?

03:20.120 --> 03:21.710
Like the cavemen did?!

03:21.710 --> 03:24.580
Okay, feels like you guys
are putting out an energy

03:24.580 --> 03:27.040
that says
I should give you some space,

03:27.040 --> 03:28.620
so I'm gonna be
out by the pool.

03:28.620 --> 03:30.880
The pool is for people
who live here,

03:30.880 --> 03:32.750
and you chose
not to live here.

03:32.750 --> 03:34.380
But, Mom,
I'm -- I'm trying --

03:34.380 --> 03:36.040
Junior,
you made a decision.

03:36.040 --> 03:38.750
You said you could
handle the real world,

03:38.750 --> 03:41.380
so it seems like
you shouldn't be swimming,

03:41.380 --> 03:43.380
and you should be
working on your life.

03:43.380 --> 03:45.290
And you will learn

03:45.290 --> 03:48.040
that an in-shower moisturizer

03:48.040 --> 03:50.000
is a working man's
pleasure.

03:51.120 --> 03:52.580
Get out of here,
Junior.

03:52.580 --> 03:54.080
Go.

03:54.080 --> 03:55.170
[ Sighs ]

03:55.170 --> 03:57.620
Look at you and me,

03:57.620 --> 03:59.080
on the same page

03:59.080 --> 04:01.790
for an old-fashioned
Junior takedown.

04:01.790 --> 04:04.290
[ Laughs ]
Ah! You had my back.

04:04.290 --> 04:05.420
Mm.

04:05.420 --> 04:07.920
Even though
it's not exfoliated.

04:07.920 --> 04:10.170
Earl,
you need to hear this.

04:10.170 --> 04:12.120
If this is about
that "Hamilton" soundtrack,

04:12.120 --> 04:13.580
I'll say it one more time --

04:13.580 --> 04:16.290
everyone doesn't have
to like everything.

04:16.290 --> 04:18.620
Jack, tell the old man
what you told me.

04:18.620 --> 04:21.080
I had this crazy dream
last night.
Mm-hmm.

04:21.080 --> 04:23.250
So, I'm at a Lakers game,

04:23.250 --> 04:25.120
and LeBron was wearing
the number 12.

04:25.120 --> 04:26.670
That's not his number.
Exactly!

04:26.670 --> 04:29.460
And then I saw there were
12 people on the court.

04:29.460 --> 04:31.790
And then there were
12 people in the stands,

04:31.790 --> 04:32.790
which is not enough people.

04:32.790 --> 04:34.120
That's a lot of 12s.

04:34.120 --> 04:36.960
Earl,
you know what this means?

04:36.960 --> 04:39.120
I think he's got
The Gift.

04:41.670 --> 04:43.500
You mean...The Gift?

04:43.500 --> 04:46.040
What is this "gift"?
Ruby: Okay.

04:46.040 --> 04:49.790
In my family,
every few generations,

04:49.790 --> 04:51.620
there's someone
who has the gift

04:51.620 --> 04:53.000
for predicting the future.

04:53.000 --> 04:54.880
The last one to have it

04:54.880 --> 04:56.290
was my Aunt Georgia.

04:56.290 --> 04:58.380
She predicted
the Miracle on Ice.

04:58.380 --> 05:00.460
I was the first Black man
to make money off hockey.

05:00.460 --> 05:01.710
There's your headstone.

05:01.710 --> 05:06.460
All right, Earl,
now, you need to take this,

05:06.460 --> 05:10.120
find Loose Craig,
and put it all on 12.

05:10.120 --> 05:12.120
I ain't played the ponies
or the numbers in weeks.

05:12.120 --> 05:13.670
I'm off gambling.

05:13.670 --> 05:15.920
Lynette has me wanting
to be a better man.

05:15.920 --> 05:17.000
Not just on the inside.

05:17.000 --> 05:18.330
On the outside,
where the laws are.

05:18.330 --> 05:21.580
Earl, come on,
think of the good times!

05:21.580 --> 05:23.710
I'm sorry, Ruby,
I can't do it.

05:23.710 --> 05:25.580
All right,
suit yourself.

05:25.580 --> 05:27.580
I'll find Loose Craig
on my own.

05:27.580 --> 05:29.330
All right?
All right.

05:29.330 --> 05:31.080
Is he still
selling those phone cases

05:31.080 --> 05:32.540
down at the swap meet?

05:32.540 --> 05:34.500
How am I supposed to know?
Ah, yeah, I'll find him.

05:34.500 --> 05:35.540
♪♪

05:35.540 --> 05:37.880
So, we sent Junior home.

05:37.880 --> 05:39.830
Then I sent him a picture
of me in the pool

05:39.830 --> 05:41.500
just to rub it in.

05:41.500 --> 05:43.500
Charlie,
I don't even know how to swim.

05:43.500 --> 05:45.750
[ Both laugh ]

05:45.750 --> 05:47.170
I tell you,
all that chlorine,

05:47.170 --> 05:48.500
it'll --
it'll change you.

05:48.500 --> 05:51.670
I remember when I first started
living on my own.

05:51.670 --> 05:53.920
I had four roommates, man.

05:53.920 --> 05:56.040
My bedroom was a closet.

05:56.040 --> 05:59.380
There were weeks
that I survived on nothing

05:59.380 --> 06:02.920
but a pound of burger meat
and two cans of beans.

06:02.920 --> 06:04.460
Well, aren't you fancy?

06:04.460 --> 06:05.540
[ Chuckles ]
Beans and meat?

06:05.540 --> 06:06.710
Yes.

06:06.710 --> 06:08.250
All I had was toast.

06:08.250 --> 06:09.710
Damn.
Yeah.

06:09.710 --> 06:11.210
Makes you appreciate it

06:11.210 --> 06:12.540
when you finally make it,
though.

06:12.540 --> 06:13.710
[ Laughs ]
Yeah, it does.
Uh-huh.

06:13.710 --> 06:14.750
[ Toaster pops ]

06:14.750 --> 06:16.620
Oh! [ Laughs ]

06:16.620 --> 06:18.120
Yeah,
I'm glad those days

06:18.120 --> 06:21.210
are way, way, way,
way behind us.

06:21.210 --> 06:22.210
[ Both chuckling ]

06:22.210 --> 06:23.790
Must suck to be Junior,
huh?

06:23.790 --> 06:25.290
Ah, sure does.

06:25.290 --> 06:27.040
Yeah, he isn't gonna know
what's coming at him.

06:27.040 --> 06:28.620
No, he doesn't.

06:28.620 --> 06:30.210
Yeah,
he's gonna crash and burn,

06:30.210 --> 06:31.710
stop that
Johnson generational wealth

06:31.710 --> 06:32.540
right in its tracks.

06:32.540 --> 06:33.620
Okay, Charlie,

06:33.620 --> 06:36.420
Junior is not going to
crash and burn, okay?

06:36.420 --> 06:40.080
He is going to grow and learn,
like us.

06:40.080 --> 06:41.460
No, he is not.

06:41.460 --> 06:42.790
Junior didn't
grow up broke.

06:42.790 --> 06:44.080
He's a tender bird.

06:44.080 --> 06:46.460
Like one of those penguins
whose parents die

06:46.460 --> 06:48.620
so it gets nursed to adulthood
by humans

06:48.620 --> 06:51.000
until they think he's big enough
to go out on his own.

06:51.000 --> 06:52.500
So they set him free
on the ice,

06:52.500 --> 06:54.250
and then a seal eats him
on day one,

06:54.250 --> 06:56.120
then Morgan Freeman
tells us

06:56.120 --> 06:58.830
it's just the way of the world
and we shouldn't cry.

06:58.830 --> 07:01.420
[ Voice breaking ] But Morgan
doesn't know my emotions.

07:01.420 --> 07:03.460
O...Okay. Uh...

07:03.460 --> 07:05.420
Junior isn't ready, Dre!

07:05.420 --> 07:08.080
You got to protect
that boy!

07:08.080 --> 07:09.580
You got to save him
in a way

07:09.580 --> 07:12.500
that Morgan
couldn't save Pongo.

07:12.500 --> 07:13.670
Who?

07:13.670 --> 07:16.620
They fed him out of
a baby bottle, Dre!

07:16.620 --> 07:18.540
Okay.
Like -- like,
why would you --

07:18.540 --> 07:19.960
why would you do that?

07:19.960 --> 07:22.540
Excuse me.

07:22.540 --> 07:23.960
♪♪

07:23.960 --> 07:25.670
So, Charlie made me think

07:25.670 --> 07:27.460
that perhaps Junior
wasn't prepared

07:27.460 --> 07:30.170
for a life of
syrup sandwiches.

07:30.170 --> 07:33.620
Which is why I invited him over
to give him a few pointers

07:33.620 --> 07:35.790
to help him survive
life on the ice.

07:35.790 --> 07:37.670
You know,
now that I don't have a job,

07:37.670 --> 07:39.460
how am I supposed
to buy furniture?

07:39.460 --> 07:42.790
Hey, man, if you got
milk crates and plywood,

07:42.790 --> 07:44.120
you got furniture.

07:44.120 --> 07:45.330
Cool.
Mm-hmm.

07:45.330 --> 07:46.790
What's a milk crate?

07:46.790 --> 07:49.460
[ Door opens ]
Bad news
for your fantasy team, Dre!

07:49.460 --> 07:50.380
What?

07:52.460 --> 07:54.330
I did surgery
on your running back.

07:54.330 --> 07:55.790
Mm.

07:55.790 --> 07:57.210
What is he doing here?

07:57.210 --> 07:58.620
Um...

07:58.620 --> 08:00.330
he's just hanging out.

08:00.330 --> 08:02.710
Can I talk to you
for a second?

08:02.710 --> 08:04.000
Sure, babe.
Okay.

08:04.000 --> 08:05.500
[ Clears throat ]
Excuse me, son.

08:08.210 --> 08:10.210
I thought we were
on the same page, Dre.

08:10.210 --> 08:11.170
[ Sniffs ]

08:11.170 --> 08:12.500
For fun, um,

08:12.500 --> 08:15.670
could you remind me
what page that is again?

08:15.670 --> 08:17.670
The one that says

08:17.670 --> 08:20.500
that he will not
treat our home

08:20.500 --> 08:22.830
like the Four Seasons.
Okay.

08:22.830 --> 08:24.880
We should be bucking him up,
not giving him room service.

08:24.880 --> 08:27.040
Okay, okay, same page.
Thank you.

08:27.040 --> 08:28.880
United front.
Thank you so much.

08:28.880 --> 08:30.500
All right. Uh, son.

08:30.500 --> 08:31.500
Mm-hmm?

08:31.500 --> 08:32.830
Uh, thank you
for coming by

08:32.830 --> 08:34.330
for this short visit

08:34.330 --> 08:36.210
that's ending with you
still broke and hungry.

08:36.210 --> 08:37.500
Oh, cool.
Okay.

08:37.500 --> 08:38.500
All right.

08:38.500 --> 08:39.710
Yeah, all right.

08:39.710 --> 08:41.620
Thank you, man.

08:41.620 --> 08:43.120
Is that cash?

08:43.120 --> 08:44.210
Huh?!

08:44.210 --> 08:46.120
Oh, my God.
Really?

08:48.620 --> 08:49.880
Babe! Okay!

08:49.880 --> 08:52.460
Okay, babe, I'm sorry,
it's the boy's fault!

08:52.460 --> 08:56.040
Man, how do you mess up
the dap cash pass, huh?

08:56.040 --> 08:57.540
How do you pay
your barber?

08:57.540 --> 08:58.540
Venmo.

08:58.540 --> 09:00.040
What?

09:00.040 --> 09:00.790
Junior,
get out of here!

09:02.380 --> 09:03.710
Get out of here,
Junior!

09:03.710 --> 09:05.250
Get out! Get out!!

09:05.250 --> 09:06.040
♪♪

09:09.540 --> 09:11.880
I thought we agreed about
how we were gonna handle this.

09:11.880 --> 09:14.290
Babe,
I was talking to Charlie --

09:14.290 --> 09:16.580
That's not how convincing
arguments start.

09:16.580 --> 09:19.040
Junior is not built
for this.

09:19.040 --> 09:20.290
What?

09:20.290 --> 09:22.540
You bought organic
his entire life.

09:22.540 --> 09:24.170
One package of Top Ramen

09:24.170 --> 09:26.120
is gonna send his body
into shock.

09:26.120 --> 09:28.080
I know what happens
to young men

09:28.080 --> 09:30.500
who don't have
a lot of boundaries.

09:30.500 --> 09:32.460
Mm-hmm.
Look at my brother
Johan.

09:32.460 --> 09:34.330
He still thinks
that hitchhiking

09:34.330 --> 09:36.580
is a legitimate form
of transportation.

09:36.580 --> 09:37.580
Mm-hmm.

09:37.580 --> 09:39.500
We got to hold the line
with Junior.

09:39.500 --> 09:40.790
We got to hold the line,
babe.

09:40.790 --> 09:42.920
Okay, babe, I...

09:42.920 --> 09:44.000
I will hold the line.

09:44.000 --> 09:45.170
Thank you.

09:45.170 --> 09:46.750
I will no longer
love Junior.

09:46.750 --> 09:48.000
Dre --
Huh.

09:48.000 --> 09:49.620
Well, that went down easy.

09:50.960 --> 09:53.080
All leather, all day.

09:53.080 --> 09:54.580
Look at that.

09:54.580 --> 09:56.460
Top, bottom, and inside.

09:56.460 --> 09:58.250
Hey!

09:58.250 --> 10:00.120
Each panel
from an Italian cow

10:00.120 --> 10:03.500
raised on wine
and Sinatra.

10:03.500 --> 10:04.880
[ Chuckles ]

10:04.880 --> 10:07.170
Damn, these fakes
are getting real good.

10:07.170 --> 10:08.620
Is this a Doobey and Durke?

10:08.620 --> 10:12.790
How dare you besmirch
a gift from The Gift?

10:12.790 --> 10:14.000
[ Chuckles ]

10:14.000 --> 10:16.290
Jack's dream number hit.

10:16.290 --> 10:19.040
Wait, my magic
got Grandma a purse?

10:19.040 --> 10:20.620
Oh, honey,
not just a purse.

10:20.620 --> 10:21.380
Look at that.

10:21.380 --> 10:23.120
Hey!

10:23.120 --> 10:24.290
Well, damn.

10:24.290 --> 10:26.000
So, Jack got lucky once.

10:26.000 --> 10:27.040
Stop hating.
I --

10:27.040 --> 10:28.460
Listen to me.

10:28.460 --> 10:31.330
Did you have another dream
last night?

10:31.330 --> 10:32.460
Jack: I did.

10:32.460 --> 10:34.460
Okay, so, look,
I'm a giant hot dog.

10:34.460 --> 10:37.380
Mustard, ketchup --
I'm talking the works.

10:37.380 --> 10:38.790
So no one's
gonna say anything.

10:38.790 --> 10:40.710
I'm the jerk?

10:40.710 --> 10:43.120
Okay, look at this.
Look at this.

10:43.120 --> 10:45.210
There are three horses
in this race

10:45.210 --> 10:47.080
named after hot dogs.

10:47.080 --> 10:50.830
Oscar Mayer, Weiner's Circle,
and Pork 'n' Beans.

10:50.830 --> 10:53.000
Now, with three horses,
you could win the --

10:53.000 --> 10:54.330
The Trifecta!

10:54.330 --> 10:56.210
I could pay for the wedding
with this!

10:56.210 --> 10:58.500
Yeah, and not
have to have a cash bar.

11:00.830 --> 11:03.000
Nope.

11:03.000 --> 11:04.170
Nope.

11:04.170 --> 11:06.170
I'm living clean.

11:06.170 --> 11:07.580
If you need me
for something else,

11:07.580 --> 11:08.750
I'll be in the back
having a drink.

11:08.750 --> 11:10.170
♪♪

11:10.170 --> 11:12.500
So, for the sake of my son,

11:12.500 --> 11:14.830
I needed to treat him
like a stranger.

11:14.830 --> 11:18.040
Unfortunately, Junior still
knows where I work.

11:18.040 --> 11:19.040
Hey.

11:19.040 --> 11:20.830
What are you
doing here?

11:20.830 --> 11:22.880
Well, you know, I haven't been
to the office in a while,

11:22.880 --> 11:24.830
and I just wanted to say
what's up to the crew.

11:24.830 --> 11:25.540
[ Chuckles ]
Mm-hmm.

11:25.540 --> 11:27.170
Hey, guys!

11:27.170 --> 11:29.540
Hey! Why didn't we deactivate
his passcard, huh?

11:29.540 --> 11:31.040
Who do I need to fire?

11:31.040 --> 11:32.710
Look,
I'm having an emergency.

11:32.710 --> 11:34.040
My car has a flat,

11:34.040 --> 11:35.580
and I just need to borrow
a little cash to fix it.

11:35.580 --> 11:38.040
Son,
you know I can't do that.

11:38.040 --> 11:40.040
You're an adult now,

11:40.040 --> 11:41.210
and it's up to you
to handle it.

11:41.210 --> 11:44.290
Hey, but in doing so,

11:44.290 --> 11:46.710
you might find out
that you're a lot stronger

11:46.710 --> 11:47.460
than what you think.

11:47.460 --> 11:49.580
Wow.

11:49.580 --> 11:52.210
You know, I thought
I needed a sandwich,

11:52.210 --> 11:53.750
but it turns out

11:53.750 --> 11:55.880
I just needed
one of your pep talks.

11:55.880 --> 11:57.710
Bring it in, big guy.

11:57.710 --> 11:58.790
Alright, hey.

11:58.790 --> 12:00.080
You know the way out.

12:00.080 --> 12:00.920
♪♪

12:00.920 --> 12:03.080
Man alive, Dre.

12:03.080 --> 12:06.040
Your son has that
"I just got cut off" look.

12:06.040 --> 12:07.960
Like when my second wife
realized

12:07.960 --> 12:09.880
there wouldn't be another ferry
off the island.

12:09.880 --> 12:10.750
Yeah. You know what?

12:10.750 --> 12:12.120
Bow and I decided

12:12.120 --> 12:13.290
not to give him
any more handouts.

12:13.290 --> 12:14.330
Mm.

12:14.330 --> 12:16.750
But I worry about Junior.

12:16.750 --> 12:18.830
Oh, my God.

12:18.830 --> 12:21.000
Am I worried
about Junior?

12:21.000 --> 12:22.500
Oh, wait,
I have an idea.

12:22.500 --> 12:24.120
Okay, you know, there's a --
a tiny social media project

12:24.120 --> 12:25.330
that just came across my desk.

12:25.330 --> 12:26.750
Too small for us,

12:26.750 --> 12:28.580
but Junior, I think,
would be great for it.

12:28.580 --> 12:30.580
Hmm.
I, too, have a lot of work

12:30.580 --> 12:32.420
that I don't feel like doing

12:32.420 --> 12:34.460
and could perhaps benefit
your son's journey.

12:34.460 --> 12:35.670
Okay.

12:35.670 --> 12:37.830
For example, my gutters.

12:37.830 --> 12:39.330
That driver's test.

12:39.330 --> 12:41.750
Finding out
how far behind I am

12:41.750 --> 12:44.750
with work as Dean
of a local university...

12:44.750 --> 12:48.290
Charlie's crazy,
but Josh's idea

12:48.290 --> 12:50.920
to give Junior a leg up
instead of a handout

12:50.920 --> 12:52.460
just might be the thing

12:52.460 --> 12:54.790
to keep Bow and me
on the same page.

12:54.790 --> 12:57.040
Hey, babe, I fixed Junior.

12:57.040 --> 12:59.380
All right?
There's this client at work

12:59.380 --> 13:01.040
that has
this terrible project,

13:01.040 --> 13:02.290
and I'm gonna help him get it

13:02.290 --> 13:03.880
so we don't
have to worry anymore.

13:06.290 --> 13:07.960
When are you gonna stop
helping Junior?

13:07.960 --> 13:10.540
Oh, see, babe,
I'm not "helping" helping.

13:10.540 --> 13:11.790
[ Stammering ]

13:11.790 --> 13:13.830
Like -- It's like
we're moving a table, right?

13:13.830 --> 13:16.170
And you're wondering
if I'm even lifting up my side.

13:16.170 --> 13:18.290
Don't you see that
he's playing you, Dre?

13:18.290 --> 13:21.790
We're in a position
to ease the way for him, Bow.

13:21.790 --> 13:24.120
This is what progress
looks like.

13:24.120 --> 13:25.790
No, Dre.

13:25.790 --> 13:29.540
This is kicking off
a lifetime of laziness.

13:29.540 --> 13:31.170
So, what am I
supposed to do?

13:31.170 --> 13:32.790
Just sit here
and do nothing?

13:32.790 --> 13:34.540
That's what I've been telling
you to do the whole time.

13:34.540 --> 13:35.920
Well, I don't think
I can do that.

13:35.920 --> 13:36.920
Oh, my God.

13:36.920 --> 13:38.500
We've always said

13:38.500 --> 13:41.330
we would do whatever it takes
to help support our kids,

13:41.330 --> 13:43.830
and now that he actually
needs our help,

13:43.830 --> 13:45.540
you want to abandon him?

13:45.540 --> 13:47.040
[ Doorbell rings ]

13:47.040 --> 13:49.000
[ Sighs ]
Who is this?

13:49.000 --> 13:50.380
Ahh...
Oh.

13:50.380 --> 13:51.500
Ah.

13:51.500 --> 13:53.380
Hey, guys!

13:53.380 --> 13:55.420
You might want to come
take a look at something.

13:56.670 --> 13:59.670
[ Snoring ]

13:59.670 --> 14:01.540
Are you happy now?

14:01.540 --> 14:02.750
He's homeless.

14:02.750 --> 14:05.210
Yeah. I am.

14:05.210 --> 14:08.830
♪♪

14:08.830 --> 14:10.210
Oh, I see!

14:10.210 --> 14:12.580
It's just your son
sleeping in the car

14:12.580 --> 14:14.420
like a homeless person,

14:14.420 --> 14:15.380
not an actual
homeless person.

14:15.380 --> 14:16.880
Okay.

14:16.880 --> 14:18.790
Okay, I got to go amend
my NextDoor post

14:18.790 --> 14:20.380
because I --

14:20.380 --> 14:22.540
[imitates typing]
I went crazy on you guys.

14:25.710 --> 14:29.710
So, son, how did you end up
sleeping in your car?

14:29.710 --> 14:32.540
Uh, so,
it's a long story.

14:32.540 --> 14:35.420
Junior: I got a parking ticket,
which wasn't my first.

14:35.420 --> 14:37.210
[ Sighs ]

14:37.210 --> 14:39.790
Then I had to use my rent money
to get that boot off,

14:39.790 --> 14:41.960
which led to Rickey and Isaiah
kicking me out.

14:41.960 --> 14:44.380
And since I didn't want
to hit you up anymore,

14:44.380 --> 14:46.380
I decided to sleep
in my car.

14:46.380 --> 14:47.790
Like a man.

14:47.790 --> 14:48.920
[ Whispering ] Hello, 911?

14:48.920 --> 14:50.210
It's Janine again.

14:50.210 --> 14:51.880
Yeah,
we've got a situation.

14:51.880 --> 14:55.580
No, I promise
this time it's real.

14:55.580 --> 14:57.330
And Black.

14:57.330 --> 14:59.580
So, I guess it wasn't
that long of a story.

14:59.580 --> 15:02.790
Well, I'm gonna get caught up
with your mother.

15:02.790 --> 15:04.620
Head upstairs
and take a shower.

15:04.620 --> 15:06.080
Whew. Thanks.
I need it.

15:06.080 --> 15:07.750
You know,
there are some things

15:07.750 --> 15:09.290
that you cannot wash
in a sink.

15:09.290 --> 15:12.290
♪♪

15:12.290 --> 15:13.750
Dre: Bow?
Mm-hmm.

15:13.750 --> 15:15.120
What the hell
is going on?

15:15.120 --> 15:17.080
You're happy that your son
is on the street?

15:17.080 --> 15:18.750
Your smile was bigger
than Janine's.

15:18.750 --> 15:21.790
Yeah, he needs this
so he can hit rock bottom.

15:21.790 --> 15:23.580
He's sleeping
in his car.

15:23.580 --> 15:26.120
How much more rock bottom
do you need?

15:26.120 --> 15:28.420
I don't know, maybe he spends
a couple more nights in his car,

15:28.420 --> 15:31.920
and he will regret
not having gone to college.

15:31.920 --> 15:34.290
So that's
what this is about.

15:34.290 --> 15:35.620
Hmm?

15:35.620 --> 15:37.250
Because he didn't
go to college,

15:37.250 --> 15:39.040
you're rooting
for him to fail.

15:39.040 --> 15:41.040
Dre, I'm not rooting
for him to fail.

15:41.040 --> 15:43.210
I just want him
to struggle to the point

15:43.210 --> 15:45.120
that things
don't work out for him,

15:45.120 --> 15:48.500
and his stupid hopes and dreams
are crushed.

15:48.500 --> 15:50.000
Mm.

15:54.040 --> 15:55.120
Oh.

15:56.710 --> 15:58.040
Oh, my God.

16:01.170 --> 16:02.540
I'm rooting
for him to fail.

16:02.540 --> 16:03.620
Mm-hmm.

16:03.620 --> 16:05.460
[ Sighs ]

16:05.460 --> 16:06.960
That's not me.

16:06.960 --> 16:08.960
I know.

16:08.960 --> 16:10.620
That's you.

16:10.620 --> 16:12.710
I know,
and it's so weird.

16:12.710 --> 16:14.120
That's very weird.

16:14.120 --> 16:15.380
My God.

16:17.120 --> 16:18.120
Are you okay, babe?

16:18.120 --> 16:21.040
I'm worried, Dre.

16:21.040 --> 16:25.250
I'm worried that he's
throwing everything away

16:25.250 --> 16:27.250
that he worked for,
everything that we worked for.

16:27.250 --> 16:28.750
Mm-hmm.

16:28.750 --> 16:31.330
All for some dream that
I do not understand at all,

16:31.330 --> 16:34.000
and he's -- he's struggling
through it all.

16:34.000 --> 16:36.540
You got to let that go.

16:36.540 --> 16:39.210
You can't control
his decisions.

16:39.210 --> 16:41.000
But they scare me.

16:42.670 --> 16:46.170
Don't you think it's scarier
being 19 years old,

16:46.170 --> 16:48.040
feeling your parents
don't support you?

16:48.040 --> 16:50.670
[ Sighs ] My God.

16:50.670 --> 16:52.880
♪♪

16:52.880 --> 16:53.880
[ Character screeching ]

16:53.880 --> 16:56.040
No! What?!

16:56.040 --> 16:58.040
Hey, Jack, there you are!

16:58.040 --> 16:59.420
Hey, listen,
I've been thinking.

16:59.420 --> 17:02.540
You had any more of them
crazy dream leads lately?

17:02.540 --> 17:04.080
I -- I thought you didn't
gamble anymore, Pops?

17:04.080 --> 17:05.580
Yeah,
that's what I thought, too,

17:05.580 --> 17:07.710
but since you got The Gift,
it's not really gambling,

17:07.710 --> 17:09.080
it's more like
an investment.

17:09.080 --> 17:10.920
I don't know
if I'd trust a hedge fund

17:10.920 --> 17:12.540
managed by Loose Craig.

17:12.540 --> 17:13.580
You know,
you need to go ahead

17:13.580 --> 17:14.920
and play that video game,
little girl.

17:14.920 --> 17:17.380
Now, listen, go ahead,
take a little cat nap,

17:17.380 --> 17:19.750
and if it helps at all,
I'm looking for something

17:19.750 --> 17:22.540
that's related to the Broncos
laying 6 1/2.

17:22.540 --> 17:23.790
Well, I'm in.

17:23.790 --> 17:24.920
Uh, just let me get
some NyQuil.
My man.

17:24.920 --> 17:27.710
Ruby:
Jack, don't bother.

17:27.710 --> 17:29.710
It was all a fluke,
Earl.

17:29.710 --> 17:31.880
I lost big
on those horses.

17:31.880 --> 17:33.960
They didn't
win, place, or show.

17:33.960 --> 17:36.210
Pork 'n' Beans never even
made it to the starting gate.

17:36.210 --> 17:39.040
Just ran wild
through the beer garden.

17:39.040 --> 17:40.250
Wait, they didn't win?

17:40.250 --> 17:41.540
What happened?

17:41.540 --> 17:43.290
You don't have The Gift,
baby.

17:43.290 --> 17:45.500
Hey.

17:45.500 --> 17:47.120
If you don't have The Gift,

17:47.120 --> 17:49.460
that means I almost made
a terrible mistake.

17:49.460 --> 17:50.750
Yep.

17:50.750 --> 17:52.670
You could've blown up
your relationship with Lynette

17:52.670 --> 17:53.920
over nothing.

17:53.920 --> 17:55.420
Oh, I got to go call her.

17:55.420 --> 17:57.580
Let her know
I was thinking about her.

17:57.580 --> 17:59.170
Yeah, you do that.

18:00.750 --> 18:05.080
Now, Jack,
this is very important.

18:05.080 --> 18:07.920
Don't you ever tell your dreams
to anyone again.

18:07.920 --> 18:09.120
You hear me?

18:09.120 --> 18:10.750
That's cool.

18:10.750 --> 18:14.580
Not like I was
super excited about it.

18:14.580 --> 18:16.620
Oh, uh,
if you will excuse me,

18:16.620 --> 18:18.460
I have to go
call Mason and tell him

18:18.460 --> 18:20.080
it's safe for him
to go to the zoo again.

18:20.080 --> 18:21.670
I knew The Gift
wasn't real.

18:21.670 --> 18:24.120
You sure?

18:24.120 --> 18:25.500
Because sometimes,

18:25.500 --> 18:28.500
there's more magic in the world
than you know.

18:28.500 --> 18:30.170
Dang, Grandma!

18:30.170 --> 18:34.620
So, if I looked up
the names of those horses,

18:34.620 --> 18:36.210
would I see
that they won?

18:36.210 --> 18:38.330
You could,

18:38.330 --> 18:40.460
but just know

18:40.460 --> 18:42.880
sometimes the best way
to love someone

18:42.880 --> 18:44.120
is to lie to 'em.

18:45.620 --> 18:47.120
Oh, yeah.

18:48.790 --> 18:51.330
Nice bracelet.

18:54.290 --> 18:56.620
If you have to smell it,
it's dirty.

18:56.620 --> 18:59.380
Don't worry,
I'm not taking anything.

18:59.380 --> 19:00.670
And I've convinced
my roommates

19:00.670 --> 19:02.620
to let me sleep upright
at the kitchen table.

19:02.620 --> 19:06.120
Junior, I just wanted
to come down here

19:06.120 --> 19:07.500
to tell you
that I love you,

19:07.500 --> 19:11.330
and I support you
unconditionally.

19:13.000 --> 19:16.170
I know
it may not seem like it

19:16.170 --> 19:19.250
because it has been
really, really hard for me

19:19.250 --> 19:21.380
to wrap my head around
your decisions of late,

19:21.380 --> 19:23.330
but I wanted you
to hear it from me.

19:23.330 --> 19:24.750
Okay?

19:24.750 --> 19:27.750
Okay, Mom.

19:27.750 --> 19:31.330
And I know I've let you down
a lot lately.

19:31.330 --> 19:34.000
And I put all of my eggs
into a no-college basket,

19:34.000 --> 19:35.580
and I kind of just
kicked that basket

19:35.580 --> 19:37.750
right down the stairs,
which was really stupid,

19:37.750 --> 19:40.380
because I just put all of
my eggs into that basket,

19:40.380 --> 19:42.500
and I really
need those eggs, Mom,

19:42.500 --> 19:43.830
because
I believe in myself,

19:43.830 --> 19:45.750
but things,
they could go terribly.

19:45.750 --> 19:47.710
They could go so bad.

19:47.710 --> 19:50.250
I mean, like "starting to take
SATs for rich kids" bad.

19:50.250 --> 19:51.290
Okay, okay, okay.

19:51.290 --> 19:52.420
Come here, sweetie.

19:52.420 --> 19:53.750
Oh, it's okay.

19:53.750 --> 19:55.580
It's okay, honey.

19:55.580 --> 19:57.250
I love you.

19:57.250 --> 20:00.540
Okay?

20:00.540 --> 20:02.460
Thanks, Mom.

20:02.460 --> 20:05.580
You can stay here
until you get on your feet.

20:05.580 --> 20:08.880
Because that way you can
focus on all of the great things

20:08.880 --> 20:11.380
that I know
you are gonna accomplish.

20:11.380 --> 20:13.620
Okay.

20:13.620 --> 20:16.750
But I promise I'm only gonna
stay here for a little bit.

20:16.750 --> 20:18.920
And while I'm here,
I'm gonna pay rent.

20:18.920 --> 20:20.580
Okay.

20:20.580 --> 20:22.620
Oh. Oh.

20:22.620 --> 20:24.960
Uh...okay.

20:24.960 --> 20:27.290
I -- I kind of just thought
that was gonna be a slide-by.

20:27.290 --> 20:28.540
[ Laughs ]
You know -- you know,

20:28.540 --> 20:30.080
when I, like,
reach for the check,

20:30.080 --> 20:31.460
but you know I'm not
gonna get it, right?
Right.

20:31.460 --> 20:32.620
[ Both laugh ]

20:32.620 --> 20:34.830
I get it.

20:34.830 --> 20:38.620
Cash, check, Venmo,
whatever's easiest, okay?

20:38.620 --> 20:41.250
All right, sweetie.
I love you, honey.

20:41.250 --> 20:42.080
Well, I'm screwed.

20:45.750 --> 20:48.420
♪♪

20:48.420 --> 20:50.420
Why are you in my fridge,
playboy?

20:50.420 --> 20:51.580
[ Chuckles ]

20:51.580 --> 20:52.750
Oh, you ain't heard?

20:52.750 --> 20:54.330
I live here now.

20:54.330 --> 20:56.080
What?

20:56.080 --> 20:59.080
Yeah. Mom patched things up
with her special boy.

20:59.080 --> 21:01.080
Seems real happy about it,
too.

21:01.080 --> 21:03.120
But we had you out.

21:03.120 --> 21:04.330
Shh.

21:04.330 --> 21:06.420
Might want to talk
to your girl about that.

21:06.420 --> 21:11.420
Oh, and by the way,
here's the rent, playboy.

21:11.420 --> 21:15.620
$50 wouldn't even pay
for my moisturizer!

21:15.620 --> 21:16.670
♪♪

21:16.670 --> 21:19.000
Now that he lives here,

21:19.000 --> 21:20.790
I kind of hate him again.

21:20.790 --> 21:23.290
Whoo! We're back.
